@page "/privacy"

@* Static-SSR content page. Plain-language privacy notice for the demo/showcase site.
   NOTE: this is a good-faith description of the showcase site's minimal data handling,
   not legal advice — have counsel review before relying on it. *@

<PageTitle>Privacy — BlazorDX</PageTitle>

<section class="dx-section">
    <h1>Privacy</h1>
    <p class="dx-section-sub">
        This is the privacy notice for <strong>blazordx.com</strong>, the public demo and
        documentation site for BlazorDX. Plain version: the site is a component showcase, and
        it collects essentially no personal data.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>No accounts, no sign-in, no forms that store your data.</strong> The demos
            run in your browser; anything you type into a demo stays on the page.</li>
        <li><strong>No analytics or advertising trackers.</strong> We do not use Google
            Analytics, pixels, or similar tools, and we do not sell or share data.</li>
        <li><strong>Standard server logs.</strong> Our hosting may briefly record technical
            request data (IP address, user agent, timestamp) to operate and secure the site.
            We do not use it to identify you.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
        The site uses only <strong>strictly necessary</strong> cookies needed for the framework
        to function securely (for example, an anti-forgery token). We set <strong>no</strong>
        advertising or analytics cookies, so there is no consent banner to click. If that ever
        changes, we will ask for consent before setting non-essential cookies.
    </p>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <p>
        Some pages load open-source libraries from a public CDN (for example, htmx from unpkg).
        Your browser contacts that CDN to fetch the script; we do not share personal data with it.
    </p>

    <h2>Your choices and rights</h2>
    <p>
        Because we do not maintain personal profiles, there is nothing to log into, unsubscribe
        from, or opt out of. If you believe we hold any information about you, you may ask us to
        access or delete it, or raise any privacy question, at
        <a href="mailto:privacy@blazordx.com">privacy@blazordx.com</a>. We will respond as
        required by applicable law.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p class="dx-demo-meta">
        We may update this notice as the site evolves. Last updated 2026-06-22.
    </p>
</section>
